column1: 1. Title: Understanding the Human Estimator
2. Source Information
-- Creator: Gary D. Boetticher, Nazim Lokhandwala, James C. Helm
Department of Computer Science, University of Houston - Clear Lake;
Houston, Texas 77058
-- Donor: Gary D. Boetticher, Nazim Lokhandwala, James C. Helm, Department of Computer Science, University Of
Houston - Clear Lake; Houston, Texas, 77058
-- Date: June, 2006
3. Past Usages:
Used as part of a paper submission by Boetticher, Lokhandwala, Helm for PROMISE 2006
4. Relevant Information:
Data was collected from a Web-based survey available at: http://nas.cl.uh.edu/boetticher/EffortEstimationSurvey.html
First portion of the survey collects user demographic information (education, work, domain experience)
Second portion of the survey requests user to assess 28 software components. The results for all components
are compared with actual results. Data contains the Mean Relative Error of the estimate.
5. Number of Instances: 122
6. Number of Attributes: 22 (21 non-class, 1 class)
7. Attribute Information:
A) YrOfBirth is year of birth of the participant
B) Gender (1 = Male, 0 = Female)
C) Nationality is the country of origin for the participant
D) NumericDegree refers to the highest education level attained. 1 = Below High School, 2 = High School, 3 = Bachelors, 4 = Masters, 5 = Ph.D.
E) TechUGCourses is the number of technical undergraduate courses (CS, CIS, Soft. Engr) taken by the particpant
F) TechGCourses is the number of technical graduate courses (CS, CIS, Soft. Engr) taken by the particpant
G) MgmtUGCourses is the number of management undergraduate courses taken by the participant
H) MgmtGCourses is the number of management graduate courses taken by the participant
I) TotalWorkshopsAttended refers to the total number of workshops attended
J) TotalConferencesAttended refers to the total number of conferences attended
K) TotalLanguages is the total number of years a person spent in developing code.
For the data below, 19 metrics based on a specific programming language, are consolidated below.
L) HWExp is hardware experience
M) SWExp is software experience
N) ProjectManagementHWExp is project managent hardware experience
O) ProjectManagementSWExp is project managent software experience
P) HWProjEstExp refers to the number of hardware projects a participant has estimated
Q) SWProjEstExp refers to the number of software projects a particpant has estimated
R) DomainExp is how many years experience a person has in electronic commerce and procurement
S) ProcIndExp refers to how many years experience does a person have in the process industry (e.g. oil and gas)
T) TimeSpentOnSurveyInMinutes is the number of minutes a user spent on the survey
U) TotalClicks refers to the number of clicks the user used during the survey.
Since each component has many help features, this attribute gives an idea of how much help a participant reviewed
W) MRE_Estimates is the Magnitude of Relative Error. A negative value means the user underestimated.
A zero value means their total estimate matches the actual estimate.
A positive value means the user over-estimated the project.
8. Please direct all correspondence to Gary D. Boetticher at boetticher@uhcl.edu
